    "Accurately identifying the heart sounds provides insight into the heart's systolic and diastolic sounds.",
    "Since the primary objective of aberrant heart sound detection is abnormality identification rather than detection, segmentation is unnecessary.",
    "As a result, many approaches have been proposed in the literature for classifying heart sounds without resorting to segmentation.",
    "Comparable outcomes are possible when combining segmentation data from different approaches.",
    "Table 1 summarizes the results of previous efforts to classify heart diseases."
